well said black and id like to add my own experiences too to this.<br>
yah, everquest is a game. thats a blunt statement. but its a game in which what would be npc's in a normal game are instead controlled by a living person somewhere else in the world. so to call it a game isnt really a just comparison. it really is a world of its own, people socialize on it, meet, and do all sorts of activities to it and it is because of this effort we put into it that makes it a world. but in the end your only going to get out of it what you are willing to put into it. if your willing to put yourself out there and talk to that person that you felt you got along with in that last group, then things are gonna be good for ya, if you solo all the time and do solitary stuff then your never gonna broaden your horizons. i know i have made up a nice base of friends which i can, and usually am, talking to all the time. but what happens is then you stop hanging out with strangers and only with friends. sure thats fine but then what happens when a lot of friends leave, you lose people to talk to. then you get really bored of the game. so thats why you need to be constantly offering yourself to people and always working to make new friends cause that way youll always have more friends than you can talk to, a cool thing to happen and then, eq is a blast cause you got friends all over the place that you can always be talking to.<br>
<br>
for me though eq is more than a game, cause ive met someone that i really do care for. when i was wandering aimlessly after many friends left i just happened ot group with a stranger and we only grouped for like a half hour in which we wandered round lost in SK. but afterwards i talked to her again and we kept talking. now me and her care more about each other than we do fora  lot of friends in RL. im not saying go out there and try to find romance, thats foolish. but if you open up and are willing to just sometimes sit and socialize with people, then you can meet some awesome people. you might have lost friends but you can stil gain more. unless your friends list is maxed out with 30people of which you still fervently talk to, update it! clear it out and go out there and make more friends! ya never know where it will take you..<br>
